FBIS3-43264 "drafr001_d_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola UNITA, Government Clashes, Activities Wrapped Up FAA on UNITA Moving Troops to Zaire MB3012175393 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 1730 GMT 30 Dec 93 MB3012175393 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] A source in the Angolan Armed Forces [FAA] General Staff reported today that the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola [UNITA] is moving troops from Huambo in an easterly direction to the Republic of Zaire, which is UNITA's logistical source. That FAA source added that two UNITA army columns are moving [words indistinct] the Republic of Zaire. That source also said that recent intensified offensive operations by UNITA have confirmed all suspicions that that movement was less than satisfied with the results of the UN inquiry into the alleged attempt on the life of UNITA leader Jonas Savimbi. That FAA source noted that [words indistinct] the Lusaka peace talks were suspended and the military operations (?resumed).
